Navigate to other release versions of Doxee Platform Business Designer

[6.6](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/business-designer-6-6)

[6.7](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/business-designer-6-7)

The meta data of a template can be viewed through the left toolbar. Any meta data can be defined locally or referenced from external .itx files for each template. Each meta data consists of a *key *and a *value*.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

The data can be edited or added (add key) by clicking on a key or a value. The meta data are automatically sorted from A-Z. Meta data can also be added from external .itx files. By clicking the folder icon in the ***Meta Data (External) ***section, you can select an external resource and the data will be listed there.

> Note

*Make sure there are no naming conflicts (duplicate key names) between local and external meta data. Naming conflicts will lead to inconsistent and unwanted behavior of the output.*
